cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CY, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes high-level abstractions for cryptographic primitives and discusses the implementation of security protocols. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the ease of writing security protocols using the proposed abstractions. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of the abstractions in Python and how they can be implemented in any language. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the safety of the proposed abstractions against cryptographic misuse reported in the literature. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the overhead of the proposed implementation.
